Teacher Rebecca Friedrichs said California’s unions are using financial dues to push a “hard left” policy of abortion in public schools, during an interview on “Fox & Friends” Tuesday.
Teachers are these … most teachers are good, loving people and many of them are against abortion, and are against sexualizing little children,” she said.
The teachers unions collect about $5 billion a year tax-free from teachers and they use that money to push their personal, social, sexual and political agenda into our schools.”LifeNews depends on the support of readers like you to combat the pro-abortion media.
“All teachers across the country, in fact, all government employees are now free to pay unions nothing,” she said.
They got many of them to sign cards that have trapped them into the unions before that [Supreme Court] case came down.